Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/gt: Reset queue_priority_hint on parking
Git-commit: 4a3859ea5240365d21f6053ee219bb240d520895
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc2
Alt-commit: 98850e96cf811dc2d0a7d0af491caff9f5d49c1e
References: git-fixes bsc#1223677 CVE-2024-26937

Originally, with strict in order execution, we could complete execution
only when the queue was empty. Preempt-to-busy allows replacement of an
active request that may complete before the preemption is processed by
HW. If that happens, the request is retired from the queue, but the
queue_priority_hint remains set, preventing direct submission until
after the next CS interrupt is processed.

This preempt-to-busy race can be triggered by the heartbeat, which will
also act as the power-management barrier and upon completion allow us to
idle the HW. We may process the completion of the heartbeat, and begin
parking the engine before the CS event that restores the
queue_priority_hint, causing us to fail the assertion that it is MIN.

